{
  "text": "The results for the INST group in both of the experiments reported here match those of many previous experiments (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ) using similar stimuli and training procedures. They show that prior exposure to complex checkerboard stimuli will facilitate subsequent discrimination between these stimuli when the stimuli are exposed according to an intermixed rather than a blocked This document is copyrighted by the American Psychological Association or one of its allied publishers.",
